WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.458 --> 00:00:15.790
<i>-Heli 30. this is U05.
-Heli 30 responding.</i>

2
00:00:15.791 --> 00:00:19.665
<i>We have a report of a car
matching last week's getaway vehicle.</i>

3
00:00:19.666 --> 00:00:23.124
<i>Blue Ford Taunus.
license plate November Victor 34550.</i>

4
00:00:23.125 --> 00:00:25.582
<i>We lost visual contact one minute ago.</i>

5
00:00:25.583 --> 00:00:27.457
<i>heading north towards Marienlyst.</i>

6
00:00:27.458 --> 00:00:29.624
<i>We're attempting to locate the car.</i>

7
00:00:29.625 --> 00:00:31.625
<i>Copy. We're heading there.</i>

8
00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:42.708
Thanks.

9
00:00:53.750 --> 00:00:54.750
Hi. boss.

10
00:00:59.541 --> 00:01:00.499
Where?

11
00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:03.415
<i>Heli 30. Going east on Marienlyst Street.</i>

12
00:01:03.416 --> 00:01:05.040
<i>I think he's seen us.</i>

13
00:01:05.041 --> 00:01:06.208
<i>He's picked up speed.</i>

14
00:01:10.375 --> 00:01:12.040
-Hi. Tom.
-Are you in a hurry?

15
00:01:12.041 --> 00:01:14.832
The lunatic from the robbery.
The getaway car has been spotted.

16
00:01:14.833 --> 00:01:16.665
Will I see you later?

17
00:01:16.666 --> 00:01:17.500
I'll call you.

18
00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.332
-Harry. wait!
<i>-U05 to all units in areas 2 and 3.</i>

19
00:01:24.333 --> 00:01:29.457
<i>Look out for a blue Ford Taunus.
license plate November Victor 34550.</i>

20
00:01:29.458 --> 00:01:31.916
Bravo 41 responding.
It's our case. we're on our way.

21
00:01:41.625 --> 00:01:45.166
Bravo 42. we're 150 meters behind.
heading toward the Majorstua intersection.

22
00:01:58.333 --> 00:02:00.333
Easy! Take it easy!

23
00:03:06.666 --> 00:03:08.457
<i>It's 10 o'clock. This is the news.</i>

24
00:03:08.458 --> 00:03:11.624
<i>More people are demanding
that the police carry firearms.</i>

25
00:03:11.625 --> 00:03:14.957
<i>as Oslo now has
more illegal weapons than ever before.</i>

26
00:03:14.958 --> 00:03:19.874
<i>and it seems that a gang related conflict
is about to escalate in the suburbs.</i>

27
00:03:19.875 --> 00:03:24.207
<i>And over to other news.
the heat wave continues in Oslo.</i>

28
00:03:24.208 --> 00:03:27.625
<i>It reached 31 degrees yesterday.</i>

29
00:04:13.083 --> 00:04:14.583
-Helge?
-Yes?

30
00:04:15.166 --> 00:04:18.624
"The person with the highest authority
will open the vault

31
00:04:18.625 --> 00:04:22.832
<i>and put the money in the black bag.
He has 30 seconds.</i>

32
00:04:22.833 --> 00:04:26.166
If it takes any longer.
the person reading this will be shot."

33
00:04:30.916 --> 00:04:32.165
-Twenty-seven…
-Yes…

34
00:04:32.166 --> 00:04:33.708
-Twenty-six…
-Wait.

35
00:04:36.625 --> 00:04:39.041
-Twenty seconds left.
-Yes. hold on. I have to…

36
00:04:41.625 --> 00:04:42.791
Seventeen…

37
00:04:43.375 --> 00:04:45.458
The green tape. Helge.

38
00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:48.916
Hold on. hold on. hold on.

39
00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:50.333
Seven.

40
00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:52.708
Five.

41
00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:00.416
-Two. Helge!
-Yes! Listen. I just have to…

42
00:05:07.625 --> 00:05:11.082
<i>-I have to open the other lock.
-Two. Helge!</i>

43
00:05:11.083 --> 00:05:13.000
-Two. Helge!
-Yes. yes. yes!

44
00:05:24.041 --> 00:05:25.458
Here.

45
00:05:28.666 --> 00:05:30.583
It took six seconds too long.

46
00:05:55.791 --> 00:05:56.750
Harry?

47
00:06:01.791 --> 00:06:03.000
Harry?

48
00:06:06.250 --> 00:06:08.958
-What the hell are you doing?
-I'm working. boss.

49
00:06:11.333 --> 00:06:14.457
That bank robbery happened
more than five years ago.

50
00:06:14.458 --> 00:06:15.374
So?

51
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:19.000
It doesn't help anyone
reopening that case. especially not you.

52
00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:21.000
Okay.

53
00:06:22.375 --> 00:06:24.791
Ellen? I need someone with people skills.

54
00:06:25.916 --> 00:06:28.291
Come on. The biometry expert is here.

55
00:06:28.916 --> 00:06:31.582
The one on loan
from Forensics in Stockholm.

56
00:06:31.583 --> 00:06:33.249
You were supposed to handle that.

57
00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:35.499
-Me?
-I told you.

58
00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:38.332
No. I just thought that you were kidding.
I don't have…

59
00:06:38.333 --> 00:06:41.458
People skills? Social competence?
Leadership abilities?

60
00:06:42.041 --> 00:06:44.707
Can you just… get a grip. okay?

61
00:06:44.708 --> 00:06:47.541
Try to deal with normal people. for once.

62
00:06:49.125 --> 00:06:52.374
-Come on.
-Hi. Beate. Harry.

63
00:06:52.375 --> 00:06:54.582
-Lønn. Beate Lønn.
-Hi. Harry.

64
00:06:54.583 --> 00:06:56.875
-Ellen Gjelten.
-So you're Swedish?

65
00:06:58.083 --> 00:07:00.500
Yeah. Uh…

66
00:07:01.041 --> 00:07:03.250
That's not… Is it a problem?

67
00:07:03.833 --> 00:07:07.750
No. I don't have anything
against Swedes… in general.

68
00:07:33.625 --> 00:07:34.458
Hey.

69
00:07:35.083 --> 00:07:36.916
You're trying out for Delta. right?

70
00:07:39.166 --> 00:07:42.375
It's 270 out of 300. Tough requirements.

71
00:07:44.250 --> 00:07:45.957
Hey. could I show you something?

72
00:07:45.958 --> 00:07:47.082
Yes. please.

73
00:07:47.083 --> 00:07:49.125
Okay. stand like you were before.

74
00:07:51.666 --> 00:07:53.208
So… this looks like shit.

75
00:07:54.416 --> 00:07:56.833
Back up the right leg. widen your stance.

76
00:07:58.291 --> 00:08:01.791
Lean forward a bit.
And relax your shoulders.

77
00:08:03.416 --> 00:08:05.083
-Relax.
-Yeah.

78
00:08:05.791 --> 00:08:07.750
Control your breathing.

79
00:08:09.208 --> 00:08:12.625
No thoughts. no feelings.
Nothing exists but the target.

80
00:08:13.791 --> 00:08:15.500
Sink into the target.

81
00:08:16.208 --> 00:08:18.375
Breathe. Fire.

82
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:20.000
Fire.

83
00:08:20.791 --> 00:08:21.791
Fire.

84
00:08:22.458 --> 00:08:23.707
Fire.

85
00:08:23.708 --> 00:08:25.166
Lower the gun.

86
00:08:27.166 --> 00:08:29.250
Look. You can do it.

87
00:08:30.541 --> 00:08:32.082
Let me know if you need help.

88
00:08:32.083 --> 00:08:33.875
TOM WAALER
DETECTIVE

89
00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:38.499
That is a Ceska zbrojovka.

90
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:42.999
They've been rare in Oslo.
but Narcotics seized one yesterday.

91
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.290
They found it during a raid in a garage
on the east side.

92
00:08:46.291 --> 00:08:47.874
Owned by Sverre Olsen.

93
00:08:47.875 --> 00:08:51.165
We knew he was a drug dealer.
but apparently. he's been selling arms.

94
00:08:51.166 --> 00:08:53.333
and has two bank robberies on his record.

95
00:08:54.291 --> 00:08:57.415
So now. you think Olsen
is the bank robber?

96
00:08:57.416 --> 00:09:00.249
No one had ever heard of
a Ceska in Oslo before that robbery.

97
00:09:00.250 --> 00:09:02.458
so either the robber is Olsen himself.

98
00:09:03.125 --> 00:09:05.582
or he sold the Ceska and knows who it is.

99
00:09:05.583 --> 00:09:08.957
Yeah. I guess we'll have to find Olsen.

100
00:09:08.958 --> 00:09:12.040
But hey. you said you needed
someone with people skills?

101
00:09:12.041 --> 00:09:13.083
Yeah.

102
00:09:14.333 --> 00:09:15.458
Look at this.

103
00:09:16.916 --> 00:09:20.999
He gets her to talk. so he won't be
identified by a voice analysis. Look.

104
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.083
Look at her reaction. What is he saying?

105
00:09:27.958 --> 00:09:32.750
To me. it looks like he's telling her
that he's going to shoot her.

106
00:09:33.250 --> 00:09:35.749
and she can't believe it.

107
00:09:35.750 --> 00:09:41.208
-It was senseless. He had the money.
-Twelve years in prison instead of 21.

108
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:44.749
What do you think?

109
00:09:44.750 --> 00:09:47.250
The report assumed that…

110
00:09:47.750 --> 00:09:50.124
He wanted to show
that he was willing to kill.

111
00:09:50.125 --> 00:09:53.082
so that the police units
in the area wouldn't follow.

112
00:09:53.083 --> 00:09:54.916
but wait for the Delta team…

113
00:09:55.958 --> 00:09:57.708
So you've read the report?

114
00:09:58.791 --> 00:10:03.333
Then. you should know that during
the car chase. one of our cars…

115
00:10:03.916 --> 00:10:05.375
crashed.

116
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:10.249
Yeah. Coordinate with Narcotics.
I'll go check Sverre Olsen's garage.

117
00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:13.708
Uh. yeah. but weren't you… yeah.

118
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:27.790
Why don't you take the elevator? It's hot.

119
00:10:27.791 --> 00:10:29.791
I just fucking love stairs.

120
00:10:36.833 --> 00:10:41.124
Hole ran down the stairs
in 30 degree heat. Did something happen?

121
00:10:41.125 --> 00:10:45.749
He got a lead on a Sverre Olsen
after the arms seizure yesterday.

122
00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:50.040
But Narcotics have got it handled.
Why is he messing around with that?

123
00:10:50.041 --> 00:10:51.625
I don't know. Ask him.

124
00:10:54.125 --> 00:10:56.500
Don't give up. boys.

125
00:11:21.916 --> 00:11:22.916
Hi!

126
00:11:52.916 --> 00:11:54.500
-Hey. you.
<i>-Hi.</i>

127
00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:56.375
I saw you called.

128
00:11:57.083 --> 00:12:00.374
<i>So… I've got an appointment
with the therapist today.</i>

129
00:12:00.375 --> 00:12:03.249
<i>so I'll be a bit late
for dinner with you and Oleg.</i>

130
00:12:03.250 --> 00:12:05.541
Oh. But that's good.

131
00:12:06.208 --> 00:12:07.458
<i>When will we see you?</i>

132
00:12:08.041 --> 00:12:11.207
Well. can't you guys just eat.
and I'll be there later?

133
00:12:11.208 --> 00:12:14.958
Yeah. no problem.
Could you pick up a bottle of wine?

134
00:12:16.458 --> 00:12:17.750
Yeah. uh…

135
00:12:18.583 --> 00:12:20.832
Yeah. are you sure? It's not…

136
00:12:20.833 --> 00:12:24.333
No. no. hey…
It'll be a willpower exercise.

137
00:12:25.083 --> 00:12:26.083
Thanks.

138
00:12:27.041 --> 00:12:28.208
I love you.

139
00:12:33.750 --> 00:12:35.291
And you love me.

140
00:12:37.916 --> 00:12:38.916
Bye.

141
00:12:39.708 --> 00:12:40.708
Bye.

142
00:12:47.333 --> 00:12:50.958
ROY KVINSVIK RACING

143
00:12:56.875 --> 00:12:58.041
Is he here?

144
00:12:59.083 --> 00:13:00.249
Sverre?

145
00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:01.250
Yeah?

146
00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:04.166
Where else would he be?

147
00:13:05.041 --> 00:13:07.000
At the other place. I guess.

148
00:13:10.125 --> 00:13:11.666
Where's the other place?

149
00:13:16.083 --> 00:13:17.750
Fuck. the cops are here again.

150
00:13:25.625 --> 00:13:26.625
Stop the car!

151
00:13:32.625 --> 00:13:33.541
Stop the car.

152
00:13:35.333 --> 00:13:36.500
Stop the car!

153
00:13:45.708 --> 00:13:48.082
Where is Sverre Olsen's other place?

154
00:13:48.083 --> 00:13:51.832
Don't say anything. Roy.
The police can't carry firearms.

155
00:13:51.833 --> 00:13:54.790
-He can't threaten you with a weapon…
-No. I know. okay?

156
00:13:54.791 --> 00:13:56.541
I'm not saying shit.

157
00:13:57.708 --> 00:14:00.833
Three hundred?
That's enough for an extra quarter. right?

158
00:14:01.458 --> 00:14:03.666
He's not allowed to bribe either.

159
00:14:04.708 --> 00:14:05.708
Fine.

160
00:14:07.041 --> 00:14:09.750
-Five hundred?
-Fuck. what are you. deaf?

161
00:14:10.833 --> 00:14:12.041
Stop it.

162
00:14:14.583 --> 00:14:15.666
A thousand.

163
00:14:19.333 --> 00:14:22.541
Yeah… I only have 800.

164
00:14:27.666 --> 00:14:29.125
Sverre Olsen.

165
00:14:29.708 --> 00:14:31.583
No. No.

166
00:14:33.541 --> 00:14:35.500
Under the bridge at Schou's Square.

167
00:14:37.625 --> 00:14:38.833
Hey!

168
00:14:39.416 --> 00:14:42.624
You're completely right.
I'm not allowed to bribe you.

169
00:14:42.625 --> 00:14:44.916
And I've promised my girl
to buy some wine.

170
00:15:05.208 --> 00:15:07.916
Hey. Are you looking for someone?

171
00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:10.916
-Sverre.
-He's not here today.

172
00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.875
But I have a lot of pretty great stuff.

173
00:15:14.791 --> 00:15:16.958
It's okay. it's okay. It's okay.

174
00:15:24.375 --> 00:15:26.749
-He's looking for me. What do I do?
-<i>Listen.</i>

175
00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:29.749
<i>We have a cabin up in Nordmarka.
I'll send you a location.</i>

176
00:15:29.750 --> 00:15:31.958
Listen to me. They took the weapons.

177
00:15:32.708 --> 00:15:33.790
I need money.

178
00:15:33.791 --> 00:15:36.540
<i>We'll cover the weapons.
You'll stay at that cabin.</i>

179
00:15:36.541 --> 00:15:39.707
<i>Don't speak to anyone
until we've got you out of the country.</i>

180
00:15:39.708 --> 00:15:43.082
<i>From then on. we might use you
as a courier when we need more.</i>

181
00:15:43.083 --> 00:15:46.375
-More? Are you planning to start a war?
<i>-Yes.</i>

182
00:15:47.500 --> 00:15:51.500
-Against whom?
<i>-Against people like you.</i>

183
00:16:04.458 --> 00:16:05.958
Fusiform gyrus.

184
00:16:07.041 --> 00:16:09.790
It's the part of the brain
that recognizes faces.

185
00:16:09.791 --> 00:16:11.666
And you've had this all your life?

186
00:16:12.250 --> 00:16:14.915
Yeah. I mean. we all have fusiform gyrus.

187
00:16:14.916 --> 00:16:16.624
It's in the brain.

188
00:16:16.625 --> 00:16:20.082
But mine has always been
a little more developed.

189
00:16:20.083 --> 00:16:22.832
So. literally speaking. you can recognize

190
00:16:22.833 --> 00:16:25.665
every face in
the Swedish criminal records?

191
00:16:25.666 --> 00:16:27.541
Yeah. And the Norwegian one.

192
00:16:28.750 --> 00:16:31.790
It was sent to me before I got here.
so I looked through it.

193
00:16:31.791 --> 00:16:34.874
That's many thousands of faces.

194
00:16:34.875 --> 00:16:38.999
-Yeah. it is a little freaky. I guess.
-No!

195
00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:41.583
What's it like working with Harry Hole?

196
00:16:43.125 --> 00:16:44.125
Harry…

197
00:16:45.041 --> 00:16:48.624
I mean… Yeah.
you might as well hear everything.

198
00:16:48.625 --> 00:16:50.040
There are rumors about Harry.

199
00:16:50.041 --> 00:16:54.082
That he got wasted
and killed a colleague in a car accident.

200
00:16:54.083 --> 00:16:56.707
That he has a bottle of whiskey
in his inner pocket

201
00:16:56.708 --> 00:16:59.833
to prove to himself that he doesn't drink.

202
00:17:00.333 --> 00:17:03.833
Harry is the best.
he's just not good at everything else.

203
00:17:04.333 --> 00:17:05.208
He's just…

204
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:09.958
…not that interested in shining.
like certain others.

205
00:17:10.791 --> 00:17:11.957
Hi. Beate.

206
00:17:11.958 --> 00:17:14.957
-Hi.
-I heard rumors you were coming.

207
00:17:14.958 --> 00:17:17.708
-Crazy that we both ended up here.
-Crazy.

208
00:17:19.208 --> 00:17:21.833
So you two know each other. I see?

209
00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:25.166
You could say that.
Is today your first day?

210
00:17:27.083 --> 00:17:30.041
It's always a bit nerve-wracking
on your first day at work.

211
00:17:31.833 --> 00:17:35.707
By the way. I heard that you and Harry
are looking into Sverre Olsen?

212
00:17:35.708 --> 00:17:38.165
Yes. that's right. Why?

213
00:17:38.166 --> 00:17:40.457
Just let me know if you need any help.

214
00:17:40.458 --> 00:17:42.583
-Thanks. I'll let Harry know.
-Okay.

215
00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:44.458
See you around.

216
00:17:48.208 --> 00:17:49.665
How do you know him?

217
00:17:49.666 --> 00:17:53.790
He was my instructor
at the Police Academy.

218
00:17:53.791 --> 00:17:56.625
So that was… a few years ago.

219
00:17:57.833 --> 00:17:58.833
Are you okay?

220
00:17:59.416 --> 00:18:00.874
Yeah. yeah. Yeah.

221
00:18:00.875 --> 00:18:03.874
But I think I have to get back to work.

222
00:18:03.875 --> 00:18:05.208
-Yeah. bye.
-Bye.

223
00:18:14.125 --> 00:18:15.583
Fuck!

224
00:18:48.041 --> 00:18:49.791
Even if I could buy this.

225
00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:54.083
it's not worth as much as you may hope.

226
00:18:55.208 --> 00:18:56.666
But it is a diamond. right?

227
00:18:57.166 --> 00:18:59.749
Yeah. of mediocre quality.

228
00:18:59.750 --> 00:19:02.915
The red color is caused
by uncrystallized carbon.

229
00:19:02.916 --> 00:19:05.499
which makes it less clear than you want.

230
00:19:05.500 --> 00:19:07.458
-How much can you give me?
-Well…

231
00:19:08.208 --> 00:19:10.666
I'm assuming you don't have
a certificate for it?

232
00:19:12.583 --> 00:19:16.041
Right. Looks like a blood diamond to me.

233
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:18.083
Are you buying it or not?

234
00:19:18.916 --> 00:19:20.625
No. like I said. I can't take it.

235
00:19:26.375 --> 00:19:27.665
STÅLE AUNE
PSYCHOLOGIST

236
00:19:27.666 --> 00:19:31.125
Hi. my name is Harry.
and I'm an alcoholic.

237
00:19:31.958 --> 00:19:35.457
And that was so hard for you to say

238
00:19:35.458 --> 00:19:37.958
that you stopped going there?

239
00:19:40.333 --> 00:19:42.083
It works for many. it's just…

240
00:19:42.708 --> 00:19:44.750
You'd rather come here.

241
00:19:46.125 --> 00:19:47.999
We work together. so…

242
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:49.291
Why now?

243
00:19:50.375 --> 00:19:52.791
You've been sober
for a long time. haven't you?

244
00:19:54.125 --> 00:19:56.833
Yeah… I've met someone.

245
00:19:57.750 --> 00:19:59.208
I knew it.

246
00:20:01.166 --> 00:20:04.708
I knew you'd never buy
such an expensive wine for yourself.

247
00:20:06.208 --> 00:20:09.833
And when you came in the door.
I could hardly recognize you.

248
00:20:10.625 --> 00:20:13.291
"He looks like a perfectly normal.
happy human being."

249
00:20:14.666 --> 00:20:17.083
Yeah. I'd just rather be safe than sorry.

250
00:20:19.666 --> 00:20:22.666
-I don't want to fuck it up.
-No.

251
00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:32.333
I heard that you've been at it again.
looking at videos of the bank robbery.

252
00:20:35.833 --> 00:20:37.082
It might be

253
00:20:37.083 --> 00:20:40.540
that if you'd solved the case quicker.

254
00:20:40.541 --> 00:20:42.625
there'd have been no accident.

255
00:20:43.208 --> 00:20:47.416
And maybe you're thinking
that Lars would have been alive.

256
00:20:48.166 --> 00:20:50.333
It's been five years. Harry.

257
00:20:51.625 --> 00:20:53.458
You have to move on.

258
00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:57.124
What does this have to do
with the fact that I've met someone?

259
00:20:57.125 --> 00:21:00.124
You're saying
that you don't want to fuck it up.

260
00:21:00.125 --> 00:21:02.541
And what is it
that always fucks it up for you?

261
00:21:03.541 --> 00:21:05.291
Your self-loathing.

262
00:21:06.833 --> 00:21:08.333
You think that's why I drink?

263
00:21:09.750 --> 00:21:11.291
What do you think?

264
00:21:14.250 --> 00:21:15.875
I drink because I'm thirsty.

265
00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:18.791
And I'm always thirsty.

266
00:21:19.750 --> 00:21:25.999
It's been two years. three months
and seven days since I last had a drink.

267
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:28.999
but I was shaking
when I went to buy this one.

268
00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:32.541
And then you came here.
thinking I have the answer?

269
00:21:33.791 --> 00:21:38.915
No. I guess I came here
to hear myself say what I just said.

270
00:21:38.916 --> 00:21:43.166
-Isn't that what you're here for?
-Okay. That's reassuring.

271
00:21:46.208 --> 00:21:47.832
You have five minutes left.

272
00:21:47.833 --> 00:21:51.791
if there's anything
you'd like to ask or tell or…

273
00:22:01.833 --> 00:22:03.249
-Hey.
-Hey.

274
00:22:03.250 --> 00:22:05.958
-Hey. looking good.
-Hey.

275
00:22:07.333 --> 00:22:08.291
Hey. Oleg.

276
00:22:09.291 --> 00:22:10.416
Oleg. say hi.

277
00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:15.040
-Yeah…
-I don't know if this one…

278
00:22:15.041 --> 00:22:16.665
No. I can drink this.

279
00:22:16.666 --> 00:22:19.540
-What's that old game called again. Mom?
<i>-Tetris.</i>

280
00:22:19.541 --> 00:22:21.165
<i>-Tetris</i> or <i>Tetris?
-Tetris.</i>

281
00:22:21.166 --> 00:22:24.957
I've told him
that your record was 17.559 points.

282
00:22:24.958 --> 00:22:27.250
I beat that easily. I got 18.000.

283
00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:30.875
We'll see about that. old man.

284
00:22:33.375 --> 00:22:34.540
How's it going?

285
00:22:34.541 --> 00:22:36.290
No informant knows where he is.

286
00:22:36.291 --> 00:22:39.957
so I asked Narcotics
to send footage from the garage

287
00:22:39.958 --> 00:22:44.000
to see if I could recognize anybody.
but the quality is so low that…

288
00:22:45.458 --> 00:22:46.666
He's a convict.

289
00:22:47.916 --> 00:22:48.999
Drugs.

290
00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:51.333
Something Kvinsvik.

291
00:22:55.833 --> 00:22:58.333
Also a convict. Drugs again.

292
00:23:00.750 --> 00:23:02.957
These guys. they're customers.

293
00:23:02.958 --> 00:23:05.665
They're in there
for maybe one or two minutes.

294
00:23:05.666 --> 00:23:09.415
They probably do not know
where Sverre Olsen is.

295
00:23:09.416 --> 00:23:14.166
This guy is in there for 20 minutes.
He knows something.

296
00:23:16.208 --> 00:23:17.666
No. I don't think so.

297
00:23:18.666 --> 00:23:19.624
Why not?

298
00:23:19.625 --> 00:23:21.125
He would have told us.

299
00:23:23.375 --> 00:23:24.666
Don't you see who it is?

300
00:23:28.041 --> 00:23:29.999
He was worse with my last boyfriend.

301
00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:31.999
He bought Oleg this Rosenborg jersey.

302
00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:34.166
and Oleg just switched teams.

303
00:23:34.666 --> 00:23:36.750
Started rooting for Molde instead.

304
00:23:38.750 --> 00:23:41.458
He's not having
an easy time finding friends. so…

305
00:23:42.958 --> 00:23:44.999
He's just scared he's going to lose me.

306
00:23:45.000 --> 00:23:49.833
He's under no obligation to accept me.
If you and I are…

307
00:23:50.916 --> 00:23:52.541
Are what?

308
00:23:55.333 --> 00:23:59.583
If you and I are going to keep this going…

309
00:24:01.583 --> 00:24:05.875
…Oleg himself has to decide
who I'll be or not be for him.

310
00:24:10.958 --> 00:24:14.207
You know what the ladies
at the police HQ always said about you?

311
00:24:14.208 --> 00:24:16.915
No. but I don't want to know either.

312
00:24:16.916 --> 00:24:21.125
They said that no one can have
all of Harry Hole.

313
00:24:21.750 --> 00:24:23.875
Because he loves his freedom too much.

314
00:24:26.333 --> 00:24:29.833
-And?
-And I have no interest in that.

315
00:24:30.916 --> 00:24:33.833
I want all of you.
or else there's no point.

316
00:24:34.958 --> 00:24:38.375
So if that is a problem.
you should tell me now.

317
00:24:51.666 --> 00:24:53.000
I just have to…

318
00:24:53.833 --> 00:24:54.916
Talk to me.

319
00:24:56.208 --> 00:24:57.208
Yeah…

320
00:24:59.208 --> 00:25:01.791
Okay. Yes. Yes. I'm on my way.

321
00:25:04.125 --> 00:25:06.707
<i>Beate Lønn has identified the person</i>

322
00:25:06.708 --> 00:25:09.832
<i>on the surveillance footage
from Sverre Olsen's garage.</i>

323
00:25:09.833 --> 00:25:11.625
<i>It's Tom Waaler!</i>

324
00:25:13.375 --> 00:25:15.291
Yeah. and what is Waaler saying?

325
00:25:15.875 --> 00:25:17.415
<i>I haven't talked to him.</i>

326
00:25:17.416 --> 00:25:20.166
<i>He's not at work.
and he's not picking up the phone.</i>

327
00:25:21.208 --> 00:25:24.666
Hey… I'll pick you up.
and we'll go to his place.

328
00:25:29.250 --> 00:25:32.125
Did she say anything
about how sure she was?

329
00:25:33.083 --> 00:25:35.832
-Seventy percent.
-Okay.

330
00:25:35.833 --> 00:25:38.082
She's pretty specific.

331
00:25:38.083 --> 00:25:39.165
<i>Yes. hello?</i>

332
00:25:39.166 --> 00:25:41.916
Hey. it's Ellen Gjelten.
can we come in please?

333
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:44.958
<i>Is it important?
I'm in the middle of something.</i>

334
00:25:45.458 --> 00:25:47.041
It'll only take five minutes.

335
00:25:55.541 --> 00:25:57.999
See you later. Sorry.

336
00:25:58.000 --> 00:25:59.000
Hi.

337
00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:09.707
Not bad for a police salary.

338
00:26:09.708 --> 00:26:11.915
I got a pretty nice inheritance.

339
00:26:11.916 --> 00:26:13.457
What do you guys want?

340
00:26:13.458 --> 00:26:16.416
You've been in contact with Sverre Olsen.

341
00:26:17.208 --> 00:26:20.875
-I thought that case was with Narcotics.
-Yes. that's right.

342
00:26:21.791 --> 00:26:25.375
But why haven't you told us about this?

343
00:26:28.208 --> 00:26:29.457
What's this?

344
00:26:29.458 --> 00:26:30.625
It's you.

345
00:26:31.750 --> 00:26:32.999
What?

346
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:35.583
-Our analysis says that this is you.
-What analysis?

347
00:26:36.375 --> 00:26:39.665
What were you doing there?
And why have you kept it a secret?

348
00:26:39.666 --> 00:26:40.958
What are you doing?

349
00:26:42.291 --> 00:26:44.125
Are you saying that this isn't you?

350
00:26:45.500 --> 00:26:49.374
You're coming here. accusing a colleague
because you've pulled out pictures

351
00:26:49.375 --> 00:26:52.457
from a recognition software
that's wrong 90% of the time.

352
00:26:52.458 --> 00:26:55.790
This isn't from some software. Tom.

353
00:26:55.791 --> 00:26:57.041
So then what…

354
00:26:59.125 --> 00:27:03.374
Did Beate Lønn convince you
that she sees things others can't see?

355
00:27:03.375 --> 00:27:06.583
Beate Lønn does see things
that others don't.

356
00:27:08.250 --> 00:27:12.666
You should know that we had a relationship
that didn't end like she wanted.

357
00:27:14.625 --> 00:27:15.750
Oh. really?

358
00:27:17.291 --> 00:27:20.540
And that's why you think
she's lying now. or?

359
00:27:20.541 --> 00:27:22.457
It's happened before.

360
00:27:22.458 --> 00:27:26.541
So if we look into where you were
when that footage was taken. you were…

361
00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:34.166
I'm either here or at work.
That's where I am.

362
00:27:44.416 --> 00:27:46.583
Did Lucas and the others go on holiday?

363
00:27:47.375 --> 00:27:48.375
I don't know.

364
00:27:51.083 --> 00:27:52.541
Is that guy coming back?

365
00:27:53.041 --> 00:27:54.458
You can say his name.

366
00:27:56.291 --> 00:28:00.416
I don't know.
It… depends on how late it gets.

367
00:28:00.916 --> 00:28:02.375
Did you give him a key?

368
00:28:02.958 --> 00:28:04.041
No.

369
00:28:04.791 --> 00:28:08.458
I can't deal with him sleeping here.
He can sleep at home.

370
00:28:10.458 --> 00:28:11.500
Okay.

371
00:28:13.416 --> 00:28:14.250
Oleg?

372
00:28:15.458 --> 00:28:18.499
-It's okay.
-Thank you.

373
00:28:18.500 --> 00:28:20.333
It has to be Waaler in that picture.

374
00:28:21.125 --> 00:28:26.291
I'm not saying that Beate Lønn is lying.
but what. 70%? That's two out of three.

375
00:28:28.250 --> 00:28:30.374
Of course. if they do have a history.

376
00:28:30.375 --> 00:28:32.874
it's not that odd that he pops up
in her head either.

377
00:28:32.875 --> 00:28:36.958
No. but I trust Beate Lønn
more than I trust Tom Waaler.

378
00:28:38.041 --> 00:28:40.499
How did it go
with the therapist. by the way?

379
00:28:40.500 --> 00:28:43.499
Aune thinks I have commitment issues.

380
00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:46.540
-Oh. he says that. does he?
-Yep.

381
00:28:46.541 --> 00:28:48.291
He says that it's because I

382
00:28:49.458 --> 00:28:52.375
lost my mom when I was a kid. and that

383
00:28:53.333 --> 00:28:59.333
my first girlfriend killed herself.
and then… yeah. that car accident.

384
00:29:01.291 --> 00:29:04.915
So then… then.
I'd rather choose to be alone.

385
00:29:04.916 --> 00:29:07.875
And then. I choose… to numb myself.

386
00:29:10.125 --> 00:29:11.625
Psycho-babble.

387
00:29:13.291 --> 00:29:17.915
Oh Christ. but that's how it is. Harry.
Love. God fucking damn it.

388
00:29:17.916 --> 00:29:21.332
Sometimes. it feels so fucking fated
that it's going to hell.

389
00:29:21.333 --> 00:29:24.457
so you just walk around.
hoping that the crash will happen soon.

390
00:29:24.458 --> 00:29:27.125
so you can just get it over with.

391
00:29:28.666 --> 00:29:29.833
Is it over?

392
00:29:33.833 --> 00:29:38.249
He was a scumbag. like you've been saying
from the start. And I'm okay. it's just…

393
00:29:38.250 --> 00:29:41.333
What did you do?
Did you throw a chair again?

394
00:29:42.583 --> 00:29:44.957
No. I actually didn't. Not this time.

395
00:29:44.958 --> 00:29:47.458
Even though he deserved it this time too.

396
00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:52.207
Thank God we humans
actually get through stuff.

397
00:29:52.208 --> 00:29:54.916
Despite everything. We do survive.

398
00:29:55.500 --> 00:29:56.666
No. we don't.

399
00:29:57.750 --> 00:30:01.416
No. we just fall apart
a little slower or a little quicker.

400
00:30:05.541 --> 00:30:06.958
You're so broken.

401
00:30:13.166 --> 00:30:15.624
By Sunday.
you're going to show Rakel Fauke

402
00:30:15.625 --> 00:30:18.374
that you love her at least three times.

403
00:30:18.375 --> 00:30:19.791
Can you do that?

404
00:30:20.625 --> 00:30:21.833
Have a good rehearsal.

405
00:30:22.750 --> 00:30:24.415
Yes. I love you too.

406
00:30:24.416 --> 00:30:25.582
-Bye.
-Bye.

407
00:30:25.583 --> 00:30:28.208
Three times. Hole! Three times!

408
00:31:26.041 --> 00:31:28.750
INVESTIGATION REPORT
BANK ROBBERY AT MAJORSTUA

409
00:31:54.416 --> 00:31:56.625
<i>Let me introduce myself.</i>

410
00:31:57.625 --> 00:32:01.541
<i>I am the creature you hoped didn't exist.</i>

411
00:32:02.166 --> 00:32:06.625
<i>I am the one who crawls out from
under your bed when you've fallen asleep.</i>

412
00:32:07.250 --> 00:32:09.957
<i>The one who sits down on your chest.</i>

413
00:32:09.958 --> 00:32:12.500
<i>puts the bit in your mouth.</i>

414
00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:14.958
<i>and rides you.</i>

415
00:32:15.458 --> 00:32:18.625
<i>Rides you all the way to Hell.</i>

416
00:32:28.625 --> 00:32:30.499
-Hi. boss. What's up?
<i>-Hey. Boris.</i>

417
00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:32.875
<i>I'd like a quarter or two.</i>

418
00:32:33.958 --> 00:32:36.333
<i>Can't you take some from your own stash?</i>

419
00:32:36.875 --> 00:32:41.874
-They raided the garage. didn't you hear?
<i>-Shit. Where will I get powder from now?</i>

420
00:32:41.875 --> 00:32:46.875
No. hey. I'll be back soon.
so don't get a new supplier just yet.

421
00:32:47.583 --> 00:32:50.165
<i>I'll send you a location.
Get here as soon as you can.</i>

422
00:32:50.166 --> 00:32:51.082
Yeah. okay.

423
00:32:51.083 --> 00:32:54.124
<i>Not a word to anyone
about my whereabouts. okay?</i>

424
00:32:54.125 --> 00:32:56.666
What the hell?
It's in the middle of the woods!

425
00:32:57.458 --> 00:32:59.957
<i>-Do you have the cash?</i>
-I'll pay you later.

426
00:32:59.958 --> 00:33:01.166
<i>No.</i>

427
00:33:02.291 --> 00:33:03.540
No?

428
00:33:03.541 --> 00:33:07.207
<i>You're the one who taught me that.
Call me when you've got the cash.</i>

429
00:33:07.208 --> 00:33:09.000
Boris? Boris…

430
00:33:10.666 --> 00:33:12.250
Fucking hell!

431
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.499
Thanks for coming with us.

432
00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:25.040
No worries.

433
00:33:25.041 --> 00:33:29.583
No. I know
that this isn't exactly… your thing.

434
00:33:30.166 --> 00:33:35.958
What? Saturday in the park?
It doesn't get any better than this.

435
00:33:37.583 --> 00:33:39.125
We're happy that you're here.

436
00:33:40.375 --> 00:33:43.832
-Does anyone want an ice cream?
-Yeah.

437
00:33:43.833 --> 00:33:46.458
-I can get it.
-No. no. no. I'll get it.

438
00:33:47.625 --> 00:33:51.875
I'm gonna go.
You guys can try to talk to each other.

439
00:33:53.625 --> 00:33:54.791
That's what people do.

440
00:33:58.208 --> 00:33:59.707
<i>His name is Boris Koupich.</i>

441
00:33:59.708 --> 00:34:02.374
<i>And what we know here at Narcotics.</i>

442
00:34:02.375 --> 00:34:06.208
<i>is at least
that he's sold drugs for Sverre Olsen.</i>

443
00:34:06.750 --> 00:34:10.165
<i>I'll send you a picture of him.
so you can see what he looks like.</i>

444
00:34:10.166 --> 00:34:13.165
<i>and you'll owe me one.</i>

445
00:34:13.166 --> 00:34:16.375
<i>Plus the repair of that chair you threw.</i>

446
00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:23.874
Boris Koupich? Where is Sverre Olsen?

447
00:34:23.875 --> 00:34:24.958
Stop!

448
00:34:25.916 --> 00:34:27.750
Just tell me where he is.

449
00:34:32.541 --> 00:34:35.541
PLAYER: OLEG_7
SCORE: 1457

450
00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:42.166
What did Mom mean
when she said it wasn't your thing?

451
00:34:44.166 --> 00:34:46.750
Too much sun and too much noise.

452
00:34:47.791 --> 00:34:49.166
Way too many people.

453
00:34:58.291 --> 00:35:00.625
Have you tried the diving tower?

454
00:35:05.166 --> 00:35:06.625
Heights aren't my thing.

455
00:35:14.083 --> 00:35:15.375
You freeze?

456
00:35:21.208 --> 00:35:24.832
When you've decided to jump.
and you're standing on the edge.

457
00:35:24.833 --> 00:35:27.833
and you just can't move.

458
00:35:28.375 --> 00:35:30.208
What do you know about that?

459
00:35:30.958 --> 00:35:32.750
Well. I've frozen too.

460
00:35:34.833 --> 00:35:36.415
Before you were going to jump?

461
00:35:36.416 --> 00:35:39.750
No. not… not that. exactly.

462
00:35:41.000 --> 00:35:43.250
I was going to save my baby sister.

463
00:35:48.833 --> 00:35:49.916
How?

464
00:35:52.708 --> 00:35:57.166
I think I was about 12.
We were taking the elevator.

465
00:35:58.875 --> 00:36:01.749
And her hair got stuck
between the wall and the elevator

466
00:36:01.750 --> 00:36:03.041
as it started.

467
00:36:05.041 --> 00:36:06.458
And you froze?

468
00:36:08.541 --> 00:36:09.625
Yeah.

469
00:36:10.750 --> 00:36:12.291
Was she okay?

470
00:36:13.541 --> 00:36:17.957
She was okay. she lost some hair. and…

471
00:36:17.958 --> 00:36:20.541
Yeah. bled some. but she healed.

472
00:36:21.833 --> 00:36:22.958
What about you?

473
00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.708
I can't take elevators.

474
00:36:29.416 --> 00:36:31.625
-You can't?
-No.

475
00:36:36.041 --> 00:36:37.041
Listen.

476
00:36:37.750 --> 00:36:42.958
If you jump off the ten-meter platform.
I'll take the elevator to the tenth floor.

477
00:36:48.375 --> 00:36:49.500
No way.

478
00:36:56.333 --> 00:36:59.208
-Talk to me.
<i>-I think I know where Sverre Olsen is.</i>

479
00:37:00.541 --> 00:37:04.875
And now. I have a location reference
to a cabin in Nordmarka.

480
00:37:06.625 --> 00:37:08.250
Are you coming. or what?

481
00:37:09.416 --> 00:37:10.833
<i>Yeah. hold on. I…</i>

482
00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:15.332
<i>The Frogner Baths?
You're a family man today!</i>

483
00:37:15.333 --> 00:37:18.957
-Yeah. but I'll talk to…
<i>-No. hey. my darling.</i>

484
00:37:18.958 --> 00:37:23.290
Seize the one opportunity that people
like us will get. Do you hear me?

485
00:37:23.291 --> 00:37:26.540
-I'll check out the location.
<i>-Fine. but hey…</i>

486
00:37:26.541 --> 00:37:30.915
-Don't do anything… I mean. no…
<i>-No confrontation. no arrests.</i>

487
00:37:30.916 --> 00:37:33.499
<i>I'm just going to check
if Boris told me the truth.</i>

488
00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:37.040
<i>If Olsen is there. I'll call the boys
who are allowed to carry firearms.</i>

489
00:37:37.041 --> 00:37:40.583
<i>-Yeah. call Delta. and then you call me.</i>
-Yes. I'll do that.

490
00:37:41.166 --> 00:37:42.125
Fine.

491
00:37:42.833 --> 00:37:44.708
-Here.
-Thanks.

492
00:37:46.291 --> 00:37:48.750
So. what did you talk about?

493
00:37:50.041 --> 00:37:52.707
-The weather.
-About the weather?

494
00:37:52.708 --> 00:37:55.375
-Yeah. that it's so fucking nice.
-Oleg…

495
00:37:55.958 --> 00:37:57.040
Sorry.

496
00:37:57.041 --> 00:37:58.583
It is fucking nice. though.

497
00:38:14.625 --> 00:38:15.666
<i>Olsen?</i>

498
00:38:16.625 --> 00:38:17.708
I need money.

499
00:38:19.250 --> 00:38:22.333
-Or I'll tell everything.
<i>-To?</i>

500
00:38:23.375 --> 00:38:24.791
The police. of course.

501
00:38:26.833 --> 00:38:29.416
<i>And you think that they'll give you money?</i>

502
00:38:32.750 --> 00:38:33.916
Maybe not.

503
00:38:37.208 --> 00:38:40.541
But they'll reduce my sentence
to a few months.

504
00:38:43.375 --> 00:38:45.125
Maybe I'll do it anyway.

505
00:38:46.666 --> 00:38:48.041
Too bad for you. of course.

506
00:38:49.750 --> 00:38:52.208
Arms trafficking
can get you four years. right?

507
00:38:55.083 --> 00:38:56.291
And everything else.

508
00:39:00.083 --> 00:39:01.958
<i>I'll consider it. Olsen.</i>

509
00:39:10.750 --> 00:39:13.915
Mom. I don't want to be called
a wuss for the rest of my life.

510
00:39:13.916 --> 00:39:17.165
I'm sure that you'll have done it
by the end of summer.

511
00:39:17.166 --> 00:39:20.040
He will jump from ten meters
before the end of summer. right?

512
00:39:20.041 --> 00:39:22.083
No. I don't think so.

513
00:39:24.375 --> 00:39:28.999
-What do you mean?
-Maybe five. but not ten.

514
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:30.041
And why not?

515
00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:32.708
Because it's high up.

516
00:39:33.291 --> 00:39:36.250
-Have you jumped from ten meters?
-No. I haven't.

517
00:39:38.166 --> 00:39:40.541
I did a death dive from seven meters once…

518
00:39:42.416 --> 00:39:43.416
I did.

519
00:39:44.875 --> 00:39:45.957
When?

520
00:39:45.958 --> 00:39:46.958
Hey.

521
00:39:47.666 --> 00:39:49.791
When I was your age.

522
00:39:50.833 --> 00:39:53.415
I snuck in after they'd closed.

523
00:39:53.416 --> 00:39:54.874
Why?

524
00:39:54.875 --> 00:39:59.125
I didn't have to deal with others watching
as I chickened out and walked down.

525
00:40:01.250 --> 00:40:03.583
No. it's fine. it's fine. Okay.

526
00:40:04.291 --> 00:40:08.582
That was Eric. He's got a contract
right now that he needs help with.

527
00:40:08.583 --> 00:40:12.916
It has to be submitted by Monday.
I need to do this now. Is that okay?

528
00:40:13.458 --> 00:40:14.416
Sure.

529
00:40:14.916 --> 00:40:17.874
-You guys can find something to do.
-We'll do that.

530
00:40:17.875 --> 00:40:20.540
-Are you sure?
-Yeah. we'll manage.

531
00:40:20.541 --> 00:40:21.375
Thank you.

532
00:40:22.208 --> 00:40:25.874
<i>…turn around
Dance for you and hop and skip and jump</i>

533
00:40:25.875 --> 00:40:31.457
<i>Wishing you from the heart all good things
And tell me. what more do you want?</i>

534
00:40:31.458 --> 00:40:34.958
<i>Congratulations</i>

535
00:40:37.041 --> 00:40:41.040
He's offered me
the Deputy Chief of Police position.

536
00:40:41.041 --> 00:40:42.250
Wow. Congratulations.

537
00:40:43.375 --> 00:40:46.707
I'll be recommending you
as the new Head of Criminal Police.

538
00:40:46.708 --> 00:40:49.333
-Me?
-Yes. it's musical chairs.

539
00:40:50.166 --> 00:40:53.665
-Yes. Head of Criminal Police.
-Here he is. Chief of Police.

540
00:40:53.666 --> 00:40:55.125
Happy birthday.

541
00:40:57.000 --> 00:40:59.041
-Hi.
-Hi.

542
00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:05.165
Anyway. anyone in your department
who you think could take your chair?

543
00:41:05.166 --> 00:41:08.333
Sure. Ellen Gjelten
has the best leadership skills.

544
00:41:08.958 --> 00:41:13.541
<i>She's great with people. has guts.
and she thinks outside the box.</i>

545
00:41:14.125 --> 00:41:14.958
But?

546
00:41:15.625 --> 00:41:18.207
Tom Waaler is the most ambitious.

547
00:41:18.208 --> 00:41:21.000
<i>and he has
the highest clear-up rate after Hole.</i>

548
00:41:22.041 --> 00:41:23.583
So tell me about Waaler.

549
00:41:24.666 --> 00:41:29.332
<i>Well. Narcotics borrowed him
from Interpol in Brussels for a case.</i>

550
00:41:29.333 --> 00:41:31.040
<i>I think he likes it here.</i>

551
00:41:31.041 --> 00:41:33.999
<i>Then. he took the authorization course
at the Academy.</i>

552
00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:36.540
<i>and transferred over to us.
Clever. tough.</i>

553
00:41:36.541 --> 00:41:41.457
<i>Knows the system.
knows how to navigate within it.</i>

554
00:41:41.458 --> 00:41:44.708
But… you don't want Harry Hole?

555
00:41:46.791 --> 00:41:49.915
No. I mean. I love Harry.
it's nothing like that. but…

556
00:41:49.916 --> 00:41:53.249
I think it would be best
if we used him for just one thing.

557
00:41:53.250 --> 00:41:55.999
<i>He's not exactly a stickler for rules.</i>

558
00:41:56.000 --> 00:42:00.500
-Are you sure that we won't get caught?
-No. we won't get caught. Step on this.

559
00:42:31.250 --> 00:42:32.291
Fuck.

560
00:42:33.791 --> 00:42:36.125
I thought I'd seen this Lotus
at the police HQ.

561
00:42:37.250 --> 00:42:40.082
Organized Crime. Isaksson. right?

562
00:42:40.083 --> 00:42:43.791
You have a good memory. Waaler.
What are you doing here?

563
00:42:45.083 --> 00:42:46.665
We got a tip.

564
00:42:46.666 --> 00:42:49.541
We're looking for a guy
who could be in a cabin up there.

565
00:42:50.166 --> 00:42:53.540
Need help? I run here all the time.
I know this place in and out.

566
00:42:53.541 --> 00:42:58.040
No. we're just ticking a box.
It's pretty logical for him to be here.

567
00:42:58.041 --> 00:42:59.249
Okay.

568
00:42:59.250 --> 00:43:00.375
Nice tights.

569
00:43:03.583 --> 00:43:04.875
Thanks.

570
00:43:07.458 --> 00:43:09.666
Okay. see you around.

571
00:43:41.041 --> 00:43:44.833
Seven meters feels…
higher than you'd think.

572
00:43:46.083 --> 00:43:50.125
-But are you sure it's deep enough?
-There's only one way to find out.

573
00:44:02.416 --> 00:44:03.791
It's deep enough.

574
00:44:19.166 --> 00:44:21.249
Yes! Mine was better than yours. right?

575
00:44:21.250 --> 00:44:25.040
No. no.
The point is to make the biggest splash.

576
00:44:25.041 --> 00:44:26.707
So I'm the champion here.

577
00:44:26.708 --> 00:44:29.916
Unless you jump from the ten-meter.
but we can do that next year.

578
00:44:46.500 --> 00:44:47.666
The Prince.

579
00:44:51.291 --> 00:44:52.333
Hello. Sverre.

580
00:44:57.333 --> 00:44:58.500
Can I have some coffee?

581
00:45:00.833 --> 00:45:02.666
<i>Delta. Falkeid speaking.</i>

582
00:45:03.666 --> 00:45:04.500
<i>Hello?</i>

583
00:45:05.708 --> 00:45:07.499
I hope you have something for me.

584
00:45:07.500 --> 00:45:09.125
I sure do.

585
00:45:22.666 --> 00:45:23.957
Wait a minute.

586
00:45:23.958 --> 00:45:25.250
There.

587
00:45:27.375 --> 00:45:28.458
There.

588
00:45:34.458 --> 00:45:36.708
<i>Hi. this is Harry. Talk to me.</i>

589
00:46:18.375 --> 00:46:19.416
Should I do it?

590
00:46:20.375 --> 00:46:24.666
Well… I don't really want
to lose to a kid. so…

591
00:46:25.208 --> 00:46:29.375
I'll give you 50 kroner if you could
please postpone this 'til next year.

592
00:46:33.375 --> 00:46:37.791
-A hundred.
-No. forget it. I'm on a police salary.

593
00:46:52.416 --> 00:46:54.874
I'm going to turn around in three seconds.

594
00:46:54.875 --> 00:46:57.750
And you know it doesn't count
if you don't have a witness.

595
00:47:00.291 --> 00:47:01.250
Three.

596
00:47:01.791 --> 00:47:02.875
Two.

597
00:47:04.375 --> 00:47:05.333
One.

598
00:47:21.333 --> 00:47:22.541
Loser.

599
00:47:23.125 --> 00:47:24.833
Now you have to take the elevator.

600
00:47:25.458 --> 00:47:29.333
-I will. Do you want to be a witness?
-No doubt.

601
00:47:29.916 --> 00:47:31.082
Talk to me.

602
00:47:31.083 --> 00:47:33.832
<i>Hey. We're finished here.
What are you guys up to?</i>

603
00:47:33.833 --> 00:47:36.166
-We've gone fishing.
<i>-Okay.</i>

604
00:47:37.750 --> 00:47:40.291
-I'll be there soon.
<i>-Okay. we're nearly done here.</i>

605
00:47:42.125 --> 00:47:45.166
This is amazing. You're so damn good.

606
00:47:45.791 --> 00:47:48.957
-Thank you.
-I'm sorry for ruining your Saturday.

607
00:47:48.958 --> 00:47:52.625
-Could I buy you a drink?
-That's fine. We'll take a rain check.

608
00:47:53.333 --> 00:47:54.708
Another time.

609
00:47:58.291 --> 00:47:59.666
HARRY HOLE CALLING

610
00:48:20.333 --> 00:48:23.041
<i>Hi. this is Ellen's voicemail. Talk to me.</i>

611
00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:42.250
What's the music called?

612
00:48:43.166 --> 00:48:44.625
This is the Ramones.

613
00:48:48.291 --> 00:48:50.250
-Heard it before?
-No.

614
00:48:50.916 --> 00:48:53.583
<i>Hi. this is Ellen's voicemail. Talk--</i>

615
00:48:55.416 --> 00:48:57.125
What are we going to tell Mom?

616
00:49:00.333 --> 00:49:02.041
That we didn't catch any fish.

617
00:49:03.041 --> 00:49:04.291
That's lying.

618
00:49:04.958 --> 00:49:05.958
Oh?

619
00:49:06.458 --> 00:49:07.875
Did you catch any fish?

620
00:49:09.916 --> 00:49:10.750
No.

621
00:49:11.250 --> 00:49:13.875
<i>Hi. this is Ellen's voicemail. Talk--</i>

622
00:49:34.500 --> 00:49:36.000
No. no. no. no…

623
00:49:51.750 --> 00:49:55.208
Tom? Tom. what are you doing?

624
00:50:00.875 --> 00:50:03.333
Tom. what are you doing?

625
00:50:04.708 --> 00:50:07.416
-Talk to me.
-What were you doing in the woods?

626
00:50:10.333 --> 00:50:11.333
Fuck!

627
00:50:18.958 --> 00:50:21.166
-Thanks.
-Yes. thank you.

628
00:50:23.916 --> 00:50:25.832
-Hi. Mom.
-Hey! Did you have a nice time?

629
00:50:25.833 --> 00:50:27.583
-Yeah.
-Yeah? Good.

630
00:50:29.625 --> 00:50:31.290
<i>-Yes?</i>
-Hi. boss. it's me.

631
00:50:31.291 --> 00:50:33.665
Listen. I've tried
to call Ellen a few times.

632
00:50:33.666 --> 00:50:37.457
She's alone
on a potentially dangerous mission.

633
00:50:37.458 --> 00:50:39.165
I don't know where she is.

634
00:50:39.166 --> 00:50:43.040
-Alone? For fuck's sake. Harry…
<i>-Yes. I know it's my responsibility.</i>

635
00:50:43.041 --> 00:50:45.750
Could you just authorize
tracking of her phone?

636
00:50:47.125 --> 00:50:50.000
-Are you worried?
-I'm always worried. boss.

637
00:50:51.791 --> 00:50:53.166
Okay. I'll take care of it.

638
00:51:01.500 --> 00:51:06.000
Tom. nothing's happened yet. I promise.

639
00:51:11.458 --> 00:51:15.332
Tom. listen to me.
I'll keep my mouth shut. I promise.

640
00:51:15.333 --> 00:51:18.374
He'll keep his mouth shut.
He'll bleed out. We'll blame him.

641
00:51:18.375 --> 00:51:22.041
Please. Hey. this isn't you.
This isn't you.

642
00:51:22.541 --> 00:51:26.249
You're a good man. I promise.
I'll keep my mouth shut. I promise.

643
00:51:26.250 --> 00:51:27.832
I don't want to do this.

644
00:51:27.833 --> 00:51:30.665
You don't need to do it.
You haven't done it yet.

645
00:51:30.666 --> 00:51:32.915
Tom. you haven't done it yet.

646
00:51:32.916 --> 00:51:34.040
I'm so sorry.

647
00:51:34.041 --> 00:51:37.250
No. it's okay.
He won't say anything and I won't say--

648
00:51:45.416 --> 00:51:46.833
Damn it.

649
00:51:48.500 --> 00:51:51.041
There. Let me see.

650
00:52:03.166 --> 00:52:07.041
Now you'll get to hold it. Like this.

651
00:52:09.625 --> 00:52:10.540
Like this.

652
00:52:10.541 --> 00:52:11.874
No!

653
00:52:11.875 --> 00:52:15.250
Sverre? Now. you aim the gun at Ellen.

654
00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:17.500
And then. you shoot her.

655
00:52:18.333 --> 00:52:19.624
Let's aim.

656
00:52:19.625 --> 00:52:23.041
A little higher.
And then. you pull the trigger.

657
00:52:24.291 --> 00:52:25.666
Pull the trigger.

658
00:52:26.291 --> 00:52:29.250
-One. two. three.
-No…

659
00:52:32.416 --> 00:52:35.375
-Can't you do it?
-Try again.

660
00:52:35.875 --> 00:52:38.957
So I'll know that I can trust you. Okay?

661
00:52:38.958 --> 00:52:39.874
Okay.

662
00:52:39.875 --> 00:52:42.666
One more time. One. two…

663
00:52:47.125 --> 00:52:48.208
Good.

664
00:53:01.916 --> 00:53:03.665
<i>Police Operations Center.</i>

665
00:53:03.666 --> 00:53:07.000
Yes. hello?
This is Detective Tom Waaler.

666
00:53:07.666 --> 00:53:09.415
<i>A colleague has been killed.</i>

667
00:53:09.416 --> 00:53:11.790
<i>I had to shoot the perpetrator
in self-defense.</i>

668
00:53:11.791 --> 00:53:14.374
<i>I'm in a cabin out in Nordmarka.</i>

669
00:53:14.375 --> 00:53:16.208
<i>Sending coordinates now.</i>

670
00:53:18.166 --> 00:53:20.166
<i>We need Forensics here at once.</i>

671
00:53:41.083 --> 00:53:42.083
Hi. Harry.

672
00:53:43.291 --> 00:53:46.165
-What's Waaler doing here?
-He was first on the scene.

673
00:53:46.166 --> 00:53:47.165
Get him out of here.

674
00:53:47.166 --> 00:53:49.540
A known perpetrator
is lying dead in there.

675
00:53:49.541 --> 00:53:51.957
-Don't go inside.
-You have to get him out of here!

676
00:53:51.958 --> 00:53:54.583
Don't go in there.
Just leave it the fuck alone.

677
00:54:57.458 --> 00:54:59.000
I'm sorry. Harry.

678
00:55:00.875 --> 00:55:02.250
I was too late.

679
00:57:04.375 --> 00:57:05.666
<i>Open your eyes.</i>

680
00:57:07.125 --> 00:57:09.541
<i>You see. it's a simple pattern.</i>

681
00:57:11.708 --> 00:57:13.750
<i>A red guiding star.</i>

682
00:57:16.750 --> 00:57:19.083
<i>A five-pointed devil's cross</i>

683
00:57:20.083 --> 00:57:21.791
<i>will show the way.</i>

684
00:57:30.458 --> 00:57:33.957
I get that the thing with Ellen was hard.
but you have to move on.

685
00:57:33.958 --> 00:57:36.249
<i>I can't keep covering for you.</i>

686
00:57:36.250 --> 00:57:38.874
<i>If I give you the authority
to investigate Waaler.</i>

687
00:57:38.875 --> 00:57:40.333
you'll be doing it on your own.

688
00:57:42.916 --> 00:57:46.457
<i>Harry. we've got a murder just now.
and I need you at work. sober.</i>

689
00:57:46.458 --> 00:57:47.499
<i>It's the police.</i>

690
00:57:47.500 --> 00:57:51.166
Lisbeth is missing.
The premiere is in 11 days.

691
00:57:51.958 --> 00:57:55.082
You haven't made a single step forward?

692
00:57:55.083 --> 00:57:57.082
<i>We have our best investigators
on the case.</i>

693
00:57:57.083 --> 00:57:58.832
This is for us.

694
00:57:58.833 --> 00:58:02.207
He wants us to know.
he wants to be admired.

695
00:58:02.208 --> 00:58:04.541
<i>At the same time.
he's not giving us anything solid.</i>

696
00:58:14.708 --> 00:58:18.332
<i>What if I agree to join
that project of yours?</i>

697
00:58:18.333 --> 00:58:21.832
<i>You carry out a mission. alone.
without asking any questions.</i>

698
00:58:21.833 --> 00:58:23.790
<i>You'll need to burn some bridges.</i>

699
00:58:23.791 --> 00:58:26.291
That's what we do.
We take out the garbage.

700
00:58:26.916 --> 00:58:29.666
<i>Come. and I'll lead the way.</i>

701
00:59:53.625 --> 00:59:58.583
Subtitle translation by: Trine Friiis
